'''Pluto mass''' (''M''<sub>♇</sub> or ''M''<sub>P</sub>) is the unit of [[mass]] equal to that of [[Pluto]]. 1 ''M''<sub>♇</sub> = {{val|1.305|0.007|e = 22|u=kg}}.<ref name="BuieGrundyYoung_2006">{{cite journal |first = Marc W. |last = Buie |first2 = William M. |last2 = Grundy |first3 = Eliot F. |last3 = Young |display-authors = 3 |first4 = Leslie A. |last4 = Young |first5 = S. Alan |last5 = Stern |title = Orbits and photometry of Pluto's satellites: Charon, S/2005 P1, and S/2005 P2 |journal = Astronomical Journal |date = 2006 |volume = 132 | issue = 1 | page = 290 |bibcode = 2006AJ....132..290B | doi=10.1086/504422 | arxiv=astro-ph/0512491 }}</ref>
One Pluto mass can be converted to: *0.784 [[Eris (dwarf planet)|Eris]] mass *0.178 [[Moon|Lunar]] mass *0.0397 [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]] mass *0.0204 [[Mars]] mass *0.00269 [[Venus]] mass *0.00219 [[Earth]] mass ({{Earth mass|link=y}})
